Sales Manager Job (Manufacturing Industrial Equipment), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Sales
Industry:
Manufacturing
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
06 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of a leading multinational company with a core focus on Industrial equipment such as Heat Transfer, Separation and Fluid Handling. Our established client has been present in Indonesia since 1993. As expansion continues, our client is seeking a sales professional for the job of Sales Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia.
Key job responsibilities will include:
Develops a business plan and sales strategy, including marcom activities, for the market that ensures attainment of company sales goals and profitability
Orders received, gross margin and net invoicing
Performance and development of the sales engineer/MU Manager
Initiates and coordinates development of action plans to penetrate new markets
Assists in the development and implementation of marketing plans as needed
Determination of a pricing strategy
Setting and implementation of the pricing policy and authorization
Provides timely, accurate, competitive pricing on all completed prospect applications submitted for pricing and approval, while striving to maintain maximum profit margin
Resolving product or service problems and disruptions and customer complaints during warranty period of unit or parts
Visit customer to maintain good relationship as needed
Creates and conducts proposal presentations
Controls expenses to meet budget guidelines
Provides all necessary reports including forecasts in an accurate and timely manner
Adheres to all company policies, procedures and business ethics codes and ensures that they are communicated and implemented within the team
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in mechanical engineering or related major from a reputable university
At least 10 years’ experience preferably related to oil and gas industry
Proficient in Microsoft Office (MS Project, MS Word, MS Excel…)
Good verbal and written command of English
Ability to perform effectively under pressure and manage competing priorities to achieve project deadlines
Self-motivated and capable of working with minimum direct supervision
Ability to adapt to changing circumstances
Leadership skills are required to marshal resources and lead the teams
Must oversee appropriate communication as necessary
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.